RNB singer Adeoluwa has released his 10  track debut album, ‘After Bells and Whistles.’ Produced entirely by Braynezee Of NakedBeatz, the album explores the genres of R&B and soul, Afrobeats, Reggae, EDM and pop. The project also features Koreey, CHR!S, Mallz, Tonni, C.A.L and Beloved Moses. ADEOLUWA’s 2018 single, ‘Let Me In’ and 2019 jam, ‘S’okan’ were also included on the album, which trended on Twitter under the hashtag #TheABAWAlbum. According to Adeoluwa, the album was “inspired by true events” and served as a “healing project” from his past relationship.